<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,152,323]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,153,179]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks</emphasis>
. As with the preceding species, this species can be tricky to identify without reference to the male genitalia. The pattern of dark maculation, when well developed, can be helpful, and the dark “knees” of the legs are unique, but this attribute is often variably expressed and is absent from some light-colored individuals. The alignment of elytral disc punctures is variable with some individuals displaying fairly regular rows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,152,323]" box="[199,1388,296,323]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
